commit.message:
Use same capture_generator across nested captures (#144)

* Use same capture_generator across nested captures

Pass the configured captured_generator (along with all other top-level engine options) when initializing each capture_generator for handling `:capture` sexps. This ensures that nested captures behave consistently for the given top-level engine configuration.

* Show deeper nesting and use distinct generator

commit.message:
Treat the capture generator separately from the main generator

It is crucial to preserve this since Temple relies on capturing to produce
strings. These changes have led to regressions.

Revert these commits:

- Fix the default value of :capture_generator (8e5c7a2c147ff31a4735d70bddd3f64425bcbae7)
- Use the specified capture_generator even for nested captures (#112, a98bc35a951526471fff4d6b5aac8d8b2a7014af)
- Change default :capture_generator to self (b0f1f6bdf8af8cbaa18f41d6cd080cc85cf27bb0)

Swap <%= and <%== in Temple::ERB::Engine

On ERB and Erubi, <%= doesn't escape an embedded expression.
At this point, this is considered a bug fix.
